result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacqueline M Robledo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intentionally Abuse Hazardous Substance, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.316(2)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: To pay the costs of the action including court appointed attorney fees.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. To pay supervision fees as ordered by the Dept. of Corrections.
Maintain full-time employment as directed by probation agent.

Not to possess or consume any controlled substances and hazardous materials without a valid prescription and then only take in the amount and frequency prescribed.   Not to possess or use any drug paraphernalia.
Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments, including AODA assessment, as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment.

records.addlTxt: Court appointed atty bill from Steve Johnson
Defendant appears on her own with Atty Johnson.

Defendant Jacqueline M Robledo in court with attorney Stephen Pleck Johnson.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file.   Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Attorney Stephen Pleck Johnson in court.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Atty Johnson had previously stated that defendant would be late for the 1:15 hearing. Case called case at 2:11 pm.  Defendant not present in court. Atty Johnson indicates defendant did appear at the Security Checkpoint, according to Dep. Bemmann, but then walked out the door. State requests bench warrant. Court orders bench warrant but holds off signing the warrant until 4:00 pm today.

Defendant Jacqueline M Robledo in court with attorney Stephen Pleck Johnson.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file.  Atty Johnson unsure of defendant's status regarding whether she qualifies for PD representation or not. Court questions defendant on missed atty fee payments. Defendant indicates her husband has now agreed to give her the $50 per month to pay toward atty fees.  Atty Johnson requests a status in October, would like to see where Brown County case is at before disposing of the Door County cases. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for September 24, 2015 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Jacqueline M Robledo in court with attorney Stephen Pleck Johnson.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Atty Johnson indicates defendant has charges pending in Brown County, would like to talk to defendant's atty in that case before proceeding. Court reminds defendant of atty fee payments due the county as May and June payments have not been made.  Atty Johnson will also look into whether defendant qualifies for PD representation or not. State has no objection to adjournment. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 03:45 pm.
